    Lyne-Hollick recursive digital filter

    filterLH.Rd

    Lyne-Hollick recursive digital filter

    filterLH(dataset, alpha = 0.925, passes = 3)

    Arguments

    dataset

    dataframe - column 1 contains dates, column 2 contains streamflow values

    alpha

    numeric - filter parameter (defaults to 0.925 following Nathan and McMahon (1990))

    passes

    numeric - number of times the filter passes over the data (typically 1-3)

    Value

    a dataframe with 3 columns and nrow = length of streamflow dataset. Column one contains streamflow in the same units as input, column two contains baseflow in the same units as input, column three contains quickflow in the same units as input.

    Examples

    filterLH(GreenRiver)
